    "To explain our first type of results, let k be a finite extension of Q.",
    "For an integer g ≥ 1 and a family m = (m p) p:prime of integers m p ≥ 0 indexed by prime numbers, let k g,m:= k(A(k)[p mp ] | A, p) be the extension field of k obtained by adjoining all coordinates of the p mp -torsion points of A for all semiabelian variety A over k of dimension ≤ g and all prime numbers p. In [OT22, Theorem 3.3], it is proved that k g,m is highly Kummerfaithful.",
    "In this paper, we consider the following larger field; let",
    "be the extension field of k obtained by adjoining all coordinates of the points in",
    "for all semiabelian variety A over k of dimension ≤ g and all prime numbers p. Note that K g,m contains k g,m as a subfield."
